  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN191.1-kilavi">talaimakaṉ ṟaṉṉeñciṟkuc collic celavaḻuṅkiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How HE prevented going by speaking to his heart.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN191.1">
        <l>attap pātirit tuyttalaip putuvī</l>
        <l>yeriyita ḻalariyō ṭiṭaipaṭa viraii</l>
        <l>vaṇtōṭṭut toṭutta paṇpeṭu kaṇṇi</l>
        <l>tōlputaic ciraṟṟaṭik kōluṭai yumaṇa</l>
        <l>rūrkkaṇ ṭaṉṉa vāram vāṅki</l>
        <l>yaruñcura mivarnta vacaiyi ṉōṉṟāṭ</l>
        <l>ṭiruntupakaṭ ṭiyampuṅ koṭumaṇi purintavar</l>
        <l>maṭiviṭu viraiyoṭu kaṭiteti rōṭi</l>
        <l>yōmaiyaṅ kāṭṭu varūum vampalark</l>
        <l>kēmañ ceppu meṉ<supplied>ṟū</supplied>ḻ nīḷiṭai</l>
        <l>yarumporu ṇacaiip pirintuṟai vallic</l>
        <l>ceṉṟuviṉai yeṉṉuti yāyi ṉaṉṟu</l>
        <l>muraiyiṉi vāḻiyeṉ ṉeñcē niraimukai</l>
        <l>mullai yaruntu melliya vākiya</l>
        <l>vaṟaleṉa virinta vuṟaliṉ cāya</l>
        <l>loli<supplied>yi</supplied>ruṅ kūntal cēṟumeṉa</l>
        <l>valiya kūṟavum vallaiyō maṟṟē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>On the long way in the sun, (10cd)</l>
        <l>where the curved bells that ring on the perfect oxen (7a-c)</l>
        <l>with flawless sturdy legs that climbed the difficult desert, (6)</l>
        <l>dragging the carts, as if they had seen [their] village, (5)</l>
        <l>of the salt merchants, possessing staffs [and] leather-covered, noisy feet, (4)</l>
        <l>with excellent chaplets in which pointed leaves are tied (3)</l>
        <l>to the soft-headed new blossoms of the trumpet flower tree by the road, (1)</l>
        <l>mixing [them] in between with flame-petaled oleander, (2)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">speak of safety (10ab)</l>
        <l>to the strangers that come to the wilderness of toothbrush trees, (9)</l>
        <l>desirously running fast towards [them], with a haste that undoes their cloths, (7df.)</l>
        <l>if, being strong [enough] to stay away, longing for wealth difficult [to make], (11)</l>
        <l>you were to go [and] speak about work, (12a-c)</l>
        <l>speak up now, oh my heart. (12d-13c)</l>
        <l>Although you speak harsh [words], would you really have the strength (17)</l>
        <l>to say “we will go!” to [her with] luxuriant dark tresses (16)</l>
        <l>of a grace sweet to experience that spread like black sand, (15)</l>
        <l>that have become soft [and] contain jasmine, with buds in rows? (13f.)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
